void cliprint(print_e type, char *prefix, char *fmt, ...);

general colored printing utility that autoinserts newlines
and also takes custom prefixes. it also does printf-like % formatting.


'print_e type' has to be 'CLI_HINT', 'CLI_WARNING', or 'CLI_ERROR'.
these types of prints are colored blue, yellow, and red respectively,
and also prefixed with 'HINT: ', 'WARN: ', and 'ERROR: '.

setting the prefix to NULL will show these prefixes.
setting it to CLI_EMPTY_PREFIX will show none.
